frameDefinitions: A Figure is located in the interior (the Profiled_region--see Locative_relation frame) of the Ground.

An Agent or Potential_hindrance keeps a Protagonist from having a State_of_affairs that they need or desire, or, despite the possibility of preventing the possession, they allow the Protagonist to have the State_of_affairs.

This frame models the semantic contribution of negation, in which the profiled content of the Negated_proposition is asserted to contrast incompatibly with a corresponding Factual_situation, which is normally implicit.
The Lender gives the Theme to the Borrower with the expectation that the Borrower will return the Theme to the Lender after a Duration of time.
A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
A Figure is located in contact with a Ground.
frameExamples: The bookmark <t>inside</t> her book was torn and written on .
His parents <t>deprived</t> him of food for days on end.
I am <t>lending</t> a student of mine my book on German modal particles.
There was a tight-fitting lid <t>on</t> the bottle .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Figure</fen> is the entity located with respect to the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> is the area that the <fen>Figure</fen> is located in.
The area or zone interior to the <fen>Ground</fen>.  This role excludes <fen>Figure</fen> and is only used in particular constructions such as the following:
The time during which the <fen>Figure</fen> was located in the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> is the force which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening, or does not prevent it.
The  is the situation, state-of-affairs, or state of having a possession that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is kept from having.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the  person who keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the person who is kept from having the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The situation which is presented as false overall. The particular focus of negation which contrasts with the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> is not separately marked.

The situation or part of situation that actually pertains, in contradistinction to the profiled situation in the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen> that is asserted not to pertain.  In spoken language and casual written language, but not in normatively edited written texts, the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> may be expressed as an unmarked clause immediately preceding or following the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen>.
The person or institution who receives the <fen>Theme</fen> from the <fen>Lender</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The person or institution who gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The object that is transferred from the <fen>Lender</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time when the lending event occurs.
The location in which the Lender lends the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen>.
The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.

I lent <fex>the book</fex> to him for a whole month, and he still hasn't read it.
